subSubSection.paragraph:
Habitus. Length 3.77-4.13 mm, width 1.53-1.70 mm, length/width ratio 2.35-2.47, widest at anterior 1/4 of elytra. Integument dark reddish-brown to black. Scales opaque white with semi-metallic golden scales interspersed throughout, occasionally semi-translucent, appearing black, with opalescent reflections. Linear setiform scales (
'setae'
) sparse throughout, minute, sub-erect to sub-recumbent, translucent, white, arranged in rows on elytral intervals, longer on humeri and venter.

Named in reference to the smooth body surface and imperceptibly minute setae; politus = polished; Latin adjective (
Brown 1956
).
